<item>
            <title>[LU-19255] mirror write functions should not round up bytes to write(!)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19255</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The functions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lfs_mirror_write
llapi_mirror_copy
llapi_mirror_copy_many
llapi_mirror_resync_many_params &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All share the same mistake, rounding up the number of bytes to write&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/warning.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; before writing out:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;/* round up to page align to make direct IO happy. */
to_write = ((bytes_read - 1) | (page_size - 1)) + 1; &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I noticed this when playing with them - copying a small input file, they round up the size to 4K and put junk padding in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll push a patch and try to include some tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
