                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="467265" author="paf0186" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2025 14:18:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A write of less than page size works fine if the starting offset is page aligned - DIO has no issue writing out the last few bytes of a file.&#160; No need to bring in buffered IO.&#160; DIO &apos;just works&apos; for this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, it&apos;s a relief knowing we have the truncate.&#160; We actually don&apos;t have it for mirror write, but that&apos;s really only used for testing, so that&apos;s probably OK.&#160; We should still fix this but it&apos;s not anything scary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="467164" author="adilger" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2025 01:19:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this is an actual bug?  In all of those functions, the mirror is truncated before the file is actually used, so it chops off the extra bytes before the mirror becomes visible.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It might be possible to change the code to check for the end of file and call &lt;tt&gt;fcntl()&lt;/tt&gt; to change over to buffered IO for this last write, but I don&apos;t know if this would make any visible performance difference.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That said, I&apos;m a bit sad that we apparently have 4 different functions that are nearly doing the same thing, and would be happy to consolidate these into a single function (possibly structured similar toh `migrate_copy_data()`, but I&apos;m not sure if they can share code or not).&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="467152" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 12 Aug 2025 22:27:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Patrick Farrell &amp;lt;pfarrell@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60684&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60684&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
